`R = runToRound 0 outerStmtIn outerWitIn { ... }` expands to `⟨(P.runToRound 0).toFun (lens.proj (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)), (P.runToRound 0).toFun (lens.wit proj (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn))⟩`.
So the input to `toFun` is `⟨transcript, ⟨prvState, outerStmtIn, outerWitIn⟩⟩` where `transcript = P.runToRound 0 (lens.proj (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn))` and `prvState = P.runToRound 0 (lens.wit proj (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn))`.
Then `toFun` applied to this gives the result.

RHS:
`R' = runToRound 0 (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn) (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn)) P` expands to `⟨(P.runToRound 0).toFun (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn), (P.runToround 0).toFun (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn))⟩`.
So the input to `toFun` is `⟨transcript', ⟨prvState', ...⟩⟩` where `transcript' = P.runToRound 0 (lens.stmt.toFunA outerStmtIn)` and `prvState' = P.runToRound 0 (lens.wit.toFunA (outerStmtIn, outerWitIn))`.
Then `toFun` applied to this gives the result.

We need to show these are equal.

